     element's own box natively (top/left/width/height on the SAME element
     that carries the depth transform) shifts its rotation origin and
     silently corrupts the depth placement. `.compound__face` carries only
     the depth (3D) transform, at the element's full, un-cropped 100%x100%
     size (correct, unshifted origin); `.compound__face-content` is the
     footprint crop + texture, plus (see computeUvCrop) a flat 2D
     `scale(-1, ...)` when this face's uv is mirrored on an axis -- safe to
     add here since this element carries no 3D transform of its own to
     corrupt. */
  .compound__face {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
  }

  .compound__face-content {
    position: absolute;
    /* The crop viewport for this face's uv sub-rect -- a background-image
       (size+position set inline per face by computeUvCrop) so only the uv
       window shows, deliberately NOT an oversized child <img> clipped via
